          <head>
            <note type="contents-note">This manuscript contains: Jacob of Batnae. The metrical discourse of Jacob of Batnae on the Crucifixion of our Lord. In total, including sub-sections, this manuscript contains 1 item.</note>
            <listRelation type="Wright-BL-Taxonomy">
              <relation name="dcterms:type" ref="http://purl.org/dc/terms/type" active="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/322" passive="#theo-single">
                <desc>Individual Authors</desc>
              </relation>
            </listRelation>
          </head>
          <msContents>
            <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="true">
              <locus from="1" to="75">Foll. 1-75</locus>
              <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/42">
                <persName xml:lang="en">Jacob of Batnae</persName>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="en">The metrical discourse of Jacob of Batnae on the Crucifixion of our Lord</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܐܡܪܐ ܕܥܠ ܙܩܝܦܘܬܗ ܕܡܪܢ<locus from="1a"/>
              </rubric>
              <note>There are no divisions marked, either in the text or on the margins.</note>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 6 7/8 in. by 4 7/8 consisting of 75 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 6, 7, 14, 15, 65, 72, 74 and 75. The quires, signed with letters, seem to have been 10 in number, but of these <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘ</foreign> is lost, and several others are imperfect, leaves being missing at the beginning, as well as after foll. 6, 7, 13, 64, 71 and 73. There are from 20 to 24 lines in each page.</p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="perg">
                <support>
                  <material>Vellum</material>
                </support>
                <extent>
                  <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="75">75 ff.</measure>
                  <dimensions type="leaf" unit="inch">
                    <height quantity="6.875">6 7/8</height>
                    <width quantity="4.875">4 7/8</width>
                  </dimensions>
                </extent>
                <collation>
                  <p>The quires, signed with letters, seem to have been 10 in number.</p>
                </collation>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Of the quires,<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘ</foreign> is lost, and several others are imperfect, leaves being missing at the beginning, as well as after foll.<locus>6</locus>, <locus>7</locus>, <locus>13</locus>, <locus>64</locus>, <locus>71</locus> and <locus>73</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p>Some of the leaves are much stained and torn, especially foll.<locus>6</locus>, <locus>7</locus>, <locus>14</locus>, <locus>15</locus>, <locus>65</locus>, <locus>72</locus>, <locus>74</locus> and <locus>75</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="20 24">
                  <p>There are from 20 to 24 lines in each page.</p>
                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="3">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                This manuscript is written in a good, regular Estrangělā of the <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="0600" notAfter="0800">viith or viiith cent</date>.
              </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <ref target="addition1">See additions.</ref>
                </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <ref target="addition2">See additions.</ref>
                </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., items below may have been listed out of folio order in Wright's catalogue.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="75b" to="75b"/>
                  <p>A note on the margin of fol.<locus from="75b">75 b</locus>, beginning with the words <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ</quote> has been carefully erased.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="1b" to="1b"/>
                  <p>Another note, on the margin of fol. <locus from="1b">1b</locus>, informs us that the volume belonged to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/360">the convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName>.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܕܡܐܡܪ̈ܐ ܕܕܝܪܐ ܩܕܝܫܬܐ ܕܒܝܬ ܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܣܩ̈ܝܛܐ. ܐܠܗܐ ܢܚܣܐ ܠܟܠ ܕܡܡܢܥ ܠܗ ܐܡܝܢ.</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
